Isn't that the point
of an interview?
No, the point of an interview

22:45.890 --> 22:49.098
is to put you on the
spot, and your point is to
pivot back to your message.

22:49.130 --> 22:51.792
And what is my message?
Castro is ruining
the department.

22:51.830 --> 22:55.038
Now, Mrs. Florrick,
your law partner

22:55.070 --> 22:56.890
is facing drug
conspiracy charges.

22:56.940 --> 22:59.932
Why shouldn't voters trust you
based on who you associate with?

22:59.970 --> 23:03.645
Because my partner is innocent
and the current state's attorney

23:03.680 --> 23:06.148
is pursuing a vendetta
against him to get back at me.

23:06.180 --> 23:08.842
Good. Stick with it--
message discipline. Um,

23:08.880 --> 23:10.814
but doesn't your law firm
also represent Lemond Bishop,

23:10.850 --> 23:12.613
the biggest drug
dealer in Chicago?
Alleged

23:12.650 --> 23:15.517
drug dealer.
Come on, Alicia--
Lemond Bishop.

23:15.560 --> 23:18.051
In our legal system, everyone

23:18.090 --> 23:20.058
deserves a vigorous defense.

23:20.090 --> 23:21.557
But not everyone deserves you.

23:21.600 --> 23:23.795
Unlike the current
state's attorney,

23:23.830 --> 23:26.663
I've seen both sides
of the courtroom.

23:26.700 --> 23:29.589
I know how and when
the system is abused.

23:29.640 --> 23:31.801
Good. Um, don't cross
your legs under the table.

23:31.840 --> 23:33.705
Why?

23:33.740 --> 23:34.729
Well, it keeps you from
sitting up straight.

23:34.780 --> 23:36.133
So cross at the ankles.

23:36.180 --> 23:38.876
Now, let's talk
about the abortion

23:38.910 --> 23:41.617
your son got for his
underage girlfriend.

23:43.180 --> 23:44.716
Is anything wrong,
Mrs. Florrick?

23:47.020 --> 23:48.908
Is this you talking, or Prady?
Prady.

23:48.960 --> 23:51.019
And always use his
first name-- Frank.

23:51.060 --> 23:54.848
Well, Frank,

23:54.900 --> 23:58.597
I obviously find this situation
very difficult.

23:58.630 --> 24:00.632
My son...

24:01.700 --> 24:02.962
No.

24:03.000 --> 24:04.661
You want my real answer?

24:04.710 --> 24:05.608
Sure.

24:05.640 --> 24:07.608
How dare you?

24:07.640 --> 24:09.505
How in the world
does it possibly

24:09.540 --> 24:11.804
impact my work as a prosecutor

24:11.850 --> 24:14.239
to ask about my family's
most vulnerable moments?

24:14.280 --> 24:15.918
Well, it's...
This city is suffering
from the worst

24:15.950 --> 24:18.089
murder spree in its history,

24:18.120 --> 24:20.657
and you're asking me
about my son's abortion?

24:20.690 --> 24:21.952
Are you frigging kidding me?

24:21.990 --> 24:24.629
Okay. Let's unpack that.

24:24.660 --> 24:26.753
Good second half, though I'm
not sure about "frigging."

24:26.790 --> 24:28.724
And bad first half.

24:28.760 --> 24:31.160
You can't personalize it,
Alicia. It's not Frank.

24:31.200 --> 24:33.794
Well, if he asks about Zach,
then it is about Frank.
Well,

24:33.840 --> 24:35.637
the passion is good, you just
have to control it. People don't

24:35.670 --> 24:37.763
necessarily hear the words,
but they get a sense of it from

24:37.810 --> 24:39.562
your tone of voice
and your arm movements.

24:39.610 --> 24:41.134
So try to keep them in check.

24:41.180 --> 24:43.740
Gotcha.
Okay.

24:43.780 --> 24:45.042
Have you heard these rumors
that your husband

