Again, this type of...
horse...

25:00.760 --> 25:05.129
Yeah, you can't...
This kind of BS. is why
people don't run for office.

25:05.170 --> 25:06.865
It's why I almost didn't run.

25:06.900 --> 25:08.731
And then I realized if I didn't,

25:08.770 --> 25:11.807
only people like Castro would.

25:11.840 --> 25:14.729
Good, good. And don't
look at the camera.

25:14.780 --> 25:17.806
Act as if it's just the two
of you talking. And watch
out for the second camera.

25:17.850 --> 25:20.205
Sometimes, in the middle of
a question, they'll cut to you
and try to catch you off guard.

25:20.250 --> 25:22.912
And don't be afraid _to
say "I don't agree With
your characterization."

25:22.950 --> 25:24.713
Okay.

25:24.750 --> 25:26.741
Anything else?

25:26.790 --> 25:28.052
Am I ready?

25:28.090 --> 25:29.216
For now.

25:29.260 --> 25:33.082
You're a bundle of optimism.

25:33.130 --> 25:36.224
Your Honor, Cary Agos
was only following the orders

25:36.260 --> 25:38.865
of his superior,
Peter Florrick,

25:38.900 --> 25:40.595
who was state's attorney
at that time.

25:40.640 --> 25:41.993
That's why we
subpoenaed him.

25:42.040 --> 25:43.962
That he is governor
is immaterial.

25:44.010 --> 25:47.878
We're only interested in his
actions as the state's attorney.

25:49.880 --> 25:52.644
Counselor.
Yeah?

25:52.680 --> 25:55.740
It's customary at this point
for you to say something.

25:55.780 --> 25:57.884
If the governor's counsel
is arguing

25:57.920 --> 26:00.184
that Peter Florrick
held some sort of privilege...
I'm not.

26:00.220 --> 26:03.053
Or even had
qualified immunity...
I'm not saying that, either.

26:03.090 --> 26:04.751
GLA'I'I':
Well, then, what are you saying?

26:04.790 --> 26:06.985
Anyone? ASA Polmar?

26:07.030 --> 26:10.864
Qualified immunity
doesn't apply here.
A little louder.

26:10.900 --> 26:12.265
Just spill it out.

26:12.300 --> 26:14.291
(clears throat)

26:17.140 --> 26:19.199
Your Honor. Sir.

26:19.240 --> 26:22.732
Ms. Lockhart is desperate
to make this hearing about

26:22.780 --> 26:24.748
Governor Florri_ck's
refusal to testify.

26:24.780 --> 26:26.247
I'm not desperate
about anything.

26:26.280 --> 26:28.748
She wants me
to put up some shield--

26:28.780 --> 26:31.089
privilege, immunity-- so that
when he doesn't take the stand,

26:31.120 --> 26:33.918
you can draw a negative
inference from that fact.

26:33.960 --> 26:36.918
The defense has to prove
Governor Florrick

26:36.960 --> 26:40.851
can offer some testimony that
would impact her client's guilt.

26:40.900 --> 26:43.198
But he can't.

26:43.230 --> 26:46.199
Mr. Agos isn't being accused
of transporting drugs

26:46.230 --> 26:48.767
against police regulations.
He's being accused

26:48.800 --> 26:50.199
of stealing drugs.

26:50.240 --> 26:51.764
DIANE: I must prove one...
RAMONA: And even the defense

26:51.810 --> 26:53.232
isn't accusing
the governor

26:53.270 --> 26:55.409
of ordering Mr. Agos
to steal these drugs,

26:55.440 --> 26:59.706
so, again: my client
has nothing to contribute here.

26:59.750 --> 27:01.911
Accordingly,
we respectfully submit

27:01.950 --> 27:03.315
the subpoena be quashed.
Immediately.

27:03.350 --> 27:07.912
And, Your Honor, we...
respectfully disagree.

27:10.360 --> 27:13.329
Proof of other crimes presented
during trial could have

27:13.360 --> 27:16.659
an enormous negative impact
on a defendant.

27:16.700 --> 27:19.066
Accordingly, the defendant
deserves every opportunity

27:19.100 --> 27:21.068
_to have such
eVIdence excluded.

27:21.100 --> 27:23.398
In this instance,
however,

27:23.440 --> 27:26.204
I cannot compel
the testimony of a witness,

27:26.240 --> 27:27.730
let alone a sitting governor.

27:27.780 --> 27:29.975
The motion to quash is granted.

27:30.010 --> 27:31.807
Prosecution has
leave to introduce

27:31.850 --> 27:33.715
evidence of
Mr. Agos' involvement

27:33.750 --> 27:36.139
in the disappearance of
the cocaine at trial.

27:36.180 --> 27:37.886
That's it.

27:37.920 --> 27:40.809
(gavelbangs)
You can go. Next.

27:40.860 --> 27:42.680
Well done.

27:42.720 --> 27:44.426
(exhales)

27:59.410 --> 28:01.230
Okay, they said,
uh, 20 more seconds.

28:01.280 --> 28:03.077
Uh, they'll
introduce you in DC,

28:03.110 --> 28:05.374
so you won't
hear that here.

28:07.110 --> 28:09.010
Okay, here we go.

28:14.360 --> 28:15.816
That's right, Jim.

28:15.860 --> 28:18.351
First the husband,
now the wife.

28:20.530 --> 28:22.157
I can always ask her.

28:22.200 --> 28:23.929
Where do you find
the time, Alicia?

28:23.970 --> 28:26.859
The time?
Yes, you-you

28:26.900 --> 28:29.789
started your own law firm,
you have responsibilities

28:29.840 --> 28:32.502
that come with your husband's
job, there's family, and now

28:32.540 --> 28:34.371
you're running for
state's attorney.

28:34.410 --> 28:36.901
Well... yes.

28:38.380 --> 28:39.938
Um, how do you prioritize?

28:39.980 --> 28:42.517
Family first, of course.
Okay,

28:42.550 --> 28:44.882
let's start with your family.
Oh, no,

28:44.920 --> 28:46.182
um, what I was going to say,

28:46.220 --> 28:48.916
is like most busy people,
I triage.

28:48.960 --> 28:52.418
How-How do your, uh, how
do your husband and kids

28:52.460 --> 28:55.190
feel about you taking
on this SA race?

28:55.230 --> 28:57.095
Fine.

28:57.130 --> 28:59.428
Peter, uh, has done the job,

28:59.470 --> 29:02.098
so he's been really helpful.

29:02.140 --> 29:04.529
And my children, growing up
in this family,

29:04.570 --> 29:08.529
understand how important
it is to do public service.

29:08.580 --> 29:10.969
Is that something you
talk about explicitly,

29:11.010 --> 29:13.171
sitting around the dinner
table, or is it a lesson

29:13.210 --> 29:16.111
they get by Florrick
family osmosis?

29:16.150 --> 29:19.881
We have, uh, dinner together,

29:19.920 --> 29:21.808
like other families. We talk.
Oh, I'm sure.

29:21.860 --> 29:24.021
1-1 was just interested...

29:24.060 --> 29:27.996
if you like to sit down and
discuss criminal justice

29:28.030 --> 29:31.158
over the chicken, or
gab about reality TV.

29:31.200 --> 29:32.997
I don't watch reality TV.

29:33.030 --> 29:35.965
Or-Or whatever. My dad
was a police officer,

29:36.000 --> 29:37.865
uh, which I thought
was fascinating,

29:37.910 --> 29:40.401
but he never wanted
to talk about that at home.

29:40.440 --> 29:43.079
For him, it was all
Chicago Bears, all the time.

29:43.110 --> 29:45.340
(laughs)

29:45.380 --> 29:48.417
What the hell?
She's braced for hardball.
She'll relax into it.

29:48.450 --> 29:52.341
One challenge in being a
prosecutor and a mom, I imagine,

29:52.390 --> 29:55.553
will be seeing the absolute
worst side of the world

29:55.590 --> 29:57.512
you're sending your kids into.

29:57.560 --> 29:59.050
Does that worry you?

29:59.090 --> 30:02.389
To the contrary, I think
it will help me remember

30:02.430 --> 30:05.593
what's at stake every time
we try an accused criminal.

30:05.630 --> 30:08.269
_ Hmm.
Something that the current

30:08.300 --> 30:10.962
state's attorney
is failing to do.

30:11.010 --> 30:12.898
Okay.

30:12.940 --> 30:15.534
Is that part of the logic
of your campaign?

30:15.580 --> 30:19.004
Replacing the-the
prosecutor machismo

30:19.050 --> 30:21.075
with the perspective of someone

30:21.120 --> 30:24.385
who's spent the majority
of her life raising kids?

30:25.920 --> 30:27.444
I'm sorry,

30:27.490 --> 30:29.617
I disagree with your
characterization of me as

30:29.660 --> 30:32.049
someone who spent the majority
of her life raising kids.

30:32.090 --> 30:35.423
Oh, I apologize.
I-I didn't mean it as an insult.

30:35.460 --> 30:36.927
ALICIA:
Oh, no, uh, there's no

30:36.960 --> 30:39.428
need... to apologize. Um...

30:39.470 --> 30:42.291
I'm proud of being a mother.

30:42.340 --> 30:46.367
I just... I've done
a lot of other things.

30:46.410 --> 30:48.537
Oh, God, oh, God.

30:48.580 --> 30:50.400
It's okay. It's okay, we
can move on from this.

30:50.440 --> 30:52.601
It was like
watching a ship go down.

30:52.650 --> 30:54.208
And I couldn't
do anything about it.

30:54.250 --> 30:56.912
It was like my-my mouth
was on automatic pilot.

30:56.950 --> 30:58.486
He Katie Couric-ed you.

30:58.520 --> 31:00.909
You think it was planned?
Serving up softballs?

31:00.960 --> 31:02.359
If she answers them earnestly,
she looks like a lightweight.

31:02.390 --> 31:04.255
If she doesn't answer them,
she looks like a prig?

31:04.290 --> 31:05.484
I need something to drink.

31:05.530 --> 31:07.282
Wait, we have something
to tell you.

31:07.330 --> 31:09.218
I did
some intel.

31:09.260 --> 31:11.160
Prady is running.

31:11.200 --> 31:14.135
How do you know?
I talked to a friend
in Warren Plep's office.

31:14.170 --> 31:15.592
They're gathering
signatures for a Prady run.

31:15.640 --> 31:17.528
And they're doing polling.
Then we're sunk.

31:17.570 --> 31:19.606
No, no, not yet.

31:19.640 --> 31:21.676
There's always a plan "B."

31:21.710 --> 31:23.678
We dirty him up. Fast.

31:23.710 --> 31:25.507
We scare him into
not running.

31:25.550 --> 31:26.676
With what?

31:26.710 --> 31:28.143
Well, leave that to us.

31:28.180 --> 31:31.149
Okay.

31:31.190 --> 31:33.283
I'm going home to get drunk.

31:33.320 --> 31:35.208
That's a joke, right?

31:35.260 --> 31:37.057
It is. I know.

31:37.090 --> 31:39.422
Don't joke.

31:39.460 --> 31:41.519
(doorbell rings)

31:41.560 --> 31:44.097
Yeah?

31:44.130 --> 31:46.189
Your bank account balance...

31:46.230 --> 31:48.562
Okay. Who are you?

31:48.600 --> 31:50.431
I'm Kalinda Sharma.

31:50.470 --> 31:51.937
You work at the crime lab.

31:51.970 --> 31:54.370
And that is
your bank account balance.

31:54.410 --> 31:58.073
And as you can see, you received
$30,000 six months ago...

31:58.110 --> 32:01.443
I'm going to go to the police
unless you answer my questions.

32:01.480 --> 32:03.448
What questions?

32:03.480 --> 32:05.186
Well, this $30,000
couldn't have come

32:05.220 --> 32:08.314
from your salary at
the crime lab, so who paid you?

32:08.360 --> 32:10.316
I won the money.

32:10.360 --> 32:12.282
Oh. How?

32:12.330 --> 32:13.649
At a riverboat casino.

32:13.690 --> 32:16.295
Oh. Which one?

32:16.330 --> 32:20.118
Tell me the truth, Liana,
or this is gonna get worse.

32:22.000 --> 32:24.332
I never did anything
like that before.

32:24.370 --> 32:26.509
Like what? _
It was my cousm.

32:26.540 --> 32:28.007
He knew the drugs were
coming through there,

32:28.040 --> 32:29.302
and he wanted them back.

32:29.340 --> 32:31.171
Who's your cousin?
I can't tell you that.

32:31.210 --> 32:32.609
You want to take the fall
for this yourself?

32:32.650 --> 32:34.675
I don't know where he is.

32:34.720 --> 32:38.178
He took off because he was
scared of Lemond Bishop.

32:38.220 --> 32:40.609
Tell me his name?

32:43.490 --> 32:46.459
(sighs)

32:46.490 --> 32:48.697
Trey Wagner.

32:52.030 --> 32:53.463
Where is he?
I don't know.

32:53.500 --> 32:55.365
(phone ringing)
I got to go.

32:55.400 --> 32:57.698
Look, do you stay
in touch with him?
No. Good-bye.

33:21.200 --> 33:24.499
*

33:40.480 --> 33:43.119
"Gary, Indiana."

34:01.840 --> 34:03.489
Hello, Trey.

34:03.540 --> 34:04.768
Ah...
No.

34:04.810 --> 34:07.062
I'm not here for Bishop.

34:07.110 --> 34:09.135
Lady, whenever I meet
you, there's trouble.

34:09.180 --> 34:11.603
Then let's talk.

34:15.520 --> 34:18.512
"Sovereignty for Me,
Not for Thee."

34:18.550 --> 34:20.188
JOHNNY:
It's a Law
Review article

34:20.220 --> 34:21.778
Frank Prady wrote
as a student.

34:21.820 --> 34:23.151
It's about how Israeli
settlements in the West Bank

34:23.190 --> 34:25.226
violate the Geneva
Convention.
Really?

34:25.260 --> 34:26.352
It'll kill him
with Jewish voters.
And

34:26.390 --> 34:27.823
evangelical
Christians.
No.

34:27.860 --> 34:30.328
No, he's right. The evangelicals
will be turned off, too.

34:30.360 --> 34:32.328
No, we're not using this.
Why?

34:32.370 --> 34:35.589
Because we don't even know
if he still believes this.

34:35.640 --> 34:37.665
What does that matter?
Because it does.

34:37.700 --> 34:40.339
And it has nothing to do with
the state's attorney's race.
Alicia,

34:40.370 --> 34:41.769
part of running is
about electability.

34:41.810 --> 34:43.175
Attitude toward Israel
goes to electability.

34:43.210 --> 34:44.541
We're not getting
involved with this.

34:44.580 --> 34:46.172
She's right.

34:46.210 --> 34:47.541
Let's have the PAC do it.
No.

34:47.580 --> 34:49.411
We're not giving it to the PAC.

34:49.450 --> 34:51.179
We are not using it.

34:51.220 --> 34:53.586
Look.

34:53.620 --> 34:56.851
I'm learning a lot
from you guys,

34:56.890 --> 34:58.619
but you need to learn something
from me, too.

34:58.660 --> 35:01.458
He'll run, you'll lose.

35:01.500 --> 35:03.127
Maybe.

35:06.870 --> 35:08.758
(door closes)

35:08.800 --> 35:11.360
What do you think? You
know her better than I do.

35:11.410 --> 35:12.809
We can't use it.

35:12.840 --> 35:16.173
We can't slip it
to the PAC, either.

35:16.210 --> 35:18.269
There might be another way.

35:18.310 --> 35:20.699
(phone ringing)

35:23.180 --> 35:25.319
Finn Polmar.

35:25.350 --> 35:26.783
_KALINDA:
You're looking for Trey Wagner?

35:26.820 --> 35:29.152
I might be.
Who am I talking to?

35:29.190 --> 35:30.657
Ifound him.

35:30.690 --> 35:32.180
He might be willing to testify.

35:32.230 --> 35:33.822
Against Cary Agos?

35:33.860 --> 35:35.327
No. Lemond Bishop.

35:35.360 --> 35:37.828
(snaps his fingers)

35:37.860 --> 35:39.225
Get Castro now.

35:39.270 --> 35:43.161
Why would he, um,
testify against Bishop?

35:43.200 --> 35:45.509
For two reasons.

35:45.540 --> 35:49.169
He feels guilty about
framing Cary Agos,
who did nothing wrong.

35:49.210 --> 35:50.802
Well, how exactly
did he frame Cary?

35:50.840 --> 35:52.569
He turned the recording on

35:52.610 --> 35:54.578
only for what the cops
wanted to hear.

35:54.620 --> 35:55.848
Okay, and what's
the second reason?

35:55.880 --> 35:57.939
You're going
to grant him immunity?

35:57.980 --> 35:59.618
And you don't want
to tell me your name?

35:59.650 --> 36:01.254
I'm only interested in justice.

36:01.290 --> 36:04.282
Agos is innocent,
Bishop is guilty.

36:04.330 --> 36:05.957
Where are you right now?

36:05.990 --> 36:09.756
I'm with Trey.
You want to talk to him?

36:09.800 --> 36:11.927
Yes, I would.

36:11.970 --> 36:15.428
Trey, you're on.

36:17.770 --> 36:19.761
So, we need to offer Wagner

36:19.810 --> 36:21.402
immunity and
protection, and then

36:21.440 --> 36:22.930
he'll testify
against Bishop.

36:22.980 --> 36:25.949
I thought he was
giving us Cary Agos.
Well,

36:25.980 --> 36:27.777
he said Agos
didn't do anything.

36:27.810 --> 36:29.744
You know, he only
offered us the lavwer

36:29.780 --> 36:31.680
because he was afraid
of turning on Bishop.

36:31.720 --> 36:34.257
But now
he's turning on Bishop.
Well,

36:34.290 --> 36:36.281
his sister's Christian. She's
convinced him to come clean.

36:36.320 --> 36:37.912
Okay, but can he connect Bishop

36:37.960 --> 36:39.985
to the $1.3 million in heroin?

36:40.030 --> 36:41.952
No, no, no,
he said that was his.

36:42.000 --> 36:43.922
He and a few other crew members
were selling that on their own.

36:43.960 --> 36:46.929
But he can connect Bishop
to other drug deliveries.

36:46.970 --> 36:48.665
He can connect them
the way he connected Agos?

36:48.700 --> 36:50.463
Well, he's turning on his boss.

36:50.500 --> 36:52.639
No, he's admitting
that he lied about Agos.

36:52.670 --> 36:54.979
Why do we trust him now?
Because we want Bishop.

36:55.010 --> 36:57.877
Yes. We want Agos
to get us to Bishop.

36:57.910 --> 37:00.378
That's the strategy.
That should continue.
Cary Agos is innocent.

37:00.410 --> 37:02.241
No, Trey says
that he's innocent.

37:02.280 --> 37:04.589
Maybe he's lying to us now.

37:04.620 --> 37:07.441
What's going on, Jim?

37:07.490 --> 37:09.913
Nothing. I think we should stick
to the original strategy.

37:19.670 --> 37:22.298
I think you should reconsider
what you just said.

37:23.300 --> 37:25.734
You don't care about Bishop.

37:26.940 --> 37:29.272
You care about Alicia Florrick.

37:30.680 --> 37:33.308
Get out of my office.

37:41.490 --> 37:43.048
You're kidding me.

37:43.090 --> 37:45.058
Nope.

37:45.090 --> 37:47.524
VVhen?

37:49.800 --> 37:51.995
Roughly four hours ago.

37:53.370 --> 37:55.065
Oh, my God.

37:55.100 --> 37:57.534
Ithought
I was having a weird day.

37:57.570 --> 37:59.333
Why? What was your day?

37:59.370 --> 38:01.838
No, no, no, no, no,
we're gonna stick with you.

38:01.880 --> 38:03.336
What...? Why?

38:03.380 --> 38:04.870
(sighs)

38:04.910 --> 38:07.049
I was disagreeing with
Castro about trial strategy.

38:07.080 --> 38:09.969
On Cary's case?
Can't tell you.

38:10.020 --> 38:13.717
I can't. I resigned, but
it's still confidential.

38:13.750 --> 38:16.856
I think you will tell me
after three more drinks.

38:16.890 --> 38:18.357
Maybe.

38:18.390 --> 38:20.688
(laughing)

38:20.730 --> 38:23.358
Wow. So, what are you gonna do?

38:23.400 --> 38:25.766
Make some money.

38:25.800 --> 38:27.529
Open my own practice.

38:27.570 --> 38:30.698
Do you have office space?

38:30.740 --> 38:32.367
No.

38:32.410 --> 38:33.968
No. I'll probably
go looking tomorrow.

38:34.010 --> 38:37.002
I may have something.
Office space. Where?

38:37.040 --> 38:39.679
The 27th floor of our building.
We're renting it out.

38:39.710 --> 38:42.076
I don't know.
It's a little bit incestuous.

38:42.120 --> 38:43.610
If we were siblings.
(laughs)

38:43.650 --> 38:46.949
I can get you a deal.
I'll think about it.

38:46.990 --> 38:49.311
So, how was your day?

38:50.820 --> 38:53.084
Well...

38:57.130 --> 39:02.033
Let me be clear.
I am pro-Israel and proud of it.

39:02.070 --> 39:05.858
So I have to disagree vehemently
with anyone who still harbors

39:05.910 --> 39:07.537
a youthful fascination
with the Palestinian cause...

39:07.570 --> 39:09.629
Got to be kidding me.

39:09.680 --> 39:11.671
REPORTER (on TV):
SA Castro made these remarks
earlier today in response...

39:11.710 --> 39:12.847
Did you see this?

39:12.880 --> 39:14.438
Yeah. I'm watching it now.

39:14.480 --> 39:15.674
I told you not
to leak that article.

39:15.720 --> 39:17.039
Alicia, I didn't.
Castro did.

39:17.080 --> 39:18.547
And you expect me
to believe that?

39:18.590 --> 39:19.682
Look, we all do
the same searches,

39:19.720 --> 39:21.039
we all find the same dirt.

39:21.090 --> 39:22.717
This is a good thing.

39:22.760 --> 39:24.751
This hurts Prady
without reflecting on you.

39:24.790 --> 39:26.678
...for the Palestinian cause...

39:26.730 --> 39:29.028
You saw the news?
I did.

39:29.060 --> 39:31.597
So, what do we do now?
Well, I don't know
if there's anything to do.

39:31.630 --> 39:34.064
I have to find out if this was
Elfman, or if Eli pushed him.

39:34.100 --> 39:35.761
What are you talking about?

39:35.800 --> 39:37.734
The leak of Prady's
anti-Israel article.

39:37.770 --> 39:41.729
No. Trey Wagner died
in a car accident last night,

39:41.780 --> 39:43.099
along with his cousin--

39:43.140 --> 39:45.005
the two people
who could help

39:45.050 --> 39:46.745
Cary and harm Bishop.

39:46.780 --> 39:48.475
We're going to meet
the new prosecutor now.

39:48.520 --> 39:49.817
I am so sorry.

39:59.890 --> 40:02.199
Good luck.

40:02.230 --> 40:05.119
(phone ringing)

40:08.670 --> 40:09.864
Yes?

40:09.900 --> 40:11.663
RECEPTIONIST:
Frank Prady is here for you.

40:11.710 --> 40:13.507
Excuse me?

40:13.540 --> 40:15.428
Frank Prady. He knows
he doesn't have an appointment,

40:15.480 --> 40:16.902
but he asked
if you have ten minutes.

40:16.940 --> 40:19.079
I... O-Okay.

40:19.110 --> 40:21.670
Hold on one second.

40:25.820 --> 40:28.186
You know what? Just send him...
send him back.

40:36.960 --> 40:39.827
(clears throat)

40:39.870 --> 40:41.690
Oh. Mr. Prady.

40:41.740 --> 40:43.230
How are you?

40:43.270 --> 40:45.238
Uh,ne.

40:45.270 --> 40:48.535
Uh, no, actually, not fine.

40:48.580 --> 40:51.140
Oh. I'm sorry. Why is that? Can
I get you something to drink?

40:51.180 --> 40:55.514
No. No. Uh... I've been
losing friends this morning.

40:55.550 --> 40:58.815
Why?
This article.
This, uh,

40:58.850 --> 41:00.511
thought project
from a while back--

41:00.550 --> 41:02.017
uh, it's been sent
to the press...

41:02.060 --> 41:03.709
CASTRO:
Let me be clear.

41:03.760 --> 41:06.126
I am pro-Israel.

41:09.800 --> 41:11.893
Yes, I, uh... I saw it.

41:11.930 --> 41:15.161
I don't like losing friends.

41:15.200 --> 41:17.634
I don't either.

41:17.670 --> 41:21.037
Uh, you asked me to endorse you.

41:21.070 --> 41:24.107
Yes, I would love
your endorsement.

41:25.310 --> 41:27.699
I'm disgusted

41:27.750 --> 41:30.048
by the personal nature
of politics.

41:30.080 --> 41:34.779
I hate campaigns being treated
like bad reality shows.

41:34.820 --> 41:36.754
How lives are exposed,

41:36.790 --> 41:38.883
and human beings treated like...

41:38.930 --> 41:41.182
commodities.

41:41.230 --> 41:43.790
Yeah. I hate it, too.

41:43.830 --> 41:45.718
So...

41:45.770 --> 41:48.125
I've decided to run
for state's attorney.

41:48.170 --> 41:52.903
The only way to change it
is to have skin in the game.

41:52.940 --> 41:54.805
So I can't endorse you.

41:54.840 --> 41:56.569
Uh, I have resigned from CBS.

41:56.610 --> 41:57.929
Uh, I intend to
run by petition.

41:57.980 --> 41:59.845
You could have called me
to say that.

41:59.880 --> 42:01.745
Yes, I could have,

42:01.780 --> 42:03.941
_ but I wanted
to give you my reasons.

42:03.980 --> 42:07.143
This-this leak of my youthful
views has changed my mind.

42:08.590 --> 42:10.785
You're such a hypocrite.

42:11.860 --> 42:13.885
Excuse me?

42:13.930 --> 42:15.898
You've known for days now
that you are running.

42:15.930 --> 42:18.819
You had me jumping through hoops
for your endorsement

42:18.870 --> 42:20.292
when you knew.

42:20.330 --> 42:21.934
You had Warren Plep out there

42:21.970 --> 42:23.961
getting you signatures,
doing your polling.

42:24.000 --> 42:26.002
So don't act like you're trying
to change the system.

42:26.040 --> 42:27.928
You are the system.

42:27.970 --> 42:30.575
Plep was doing that on his own.
He was the one pitching me.

42:30.610 --> 42:31.872
I think we're done here,
Mr. Prady.

42:31.910 --> 42:33.207
I didn't decide to run

42:33.250 --> 42:34.774
until this leak today.

42:34.820 --> 42:37.948
Eli, he's running.
He's in my office.

42:37.980 --> 42:39.982
I intended to support you
until I discovered

42:40.020 --> 42:42.784
it was your team
that gave my article to Castro.

42:42.820 --> 42:44.981
Is there something else
you need, Mr. Prady?

42:47.230 --> 42:49.323
No.

42:49.360 --> 42:51.157
Good luck, Mrs. Florrick.

42:51.200 --> 42:53.919
Yup, it was fun.
See you out there.

